"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (e)(1), the words “government of a foreign country” are substituted for “foreign nation” for consistency in the revised title and with other titles of the United States Code.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idec022eaf-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/287"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–287","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This amends 49:70117(b)(2) by updating a cross-reference. Section 4 of the Land Remote Sensing Policy Act of 1992 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/555"},"text":"Public Law 102–555","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/4166"},"text":"106 Stat. 4166","children":[],"tail":") repealed the Land Remote-Sensing Commercialization Act of 1984 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s4201"},"text":"15 U.S.C. 4201","children":[],"tail":" et seq.). The substantive provisions of the Land Remote Sensing Policy Act of 1992, which replaced the Land Remote-Sensing Commercialization Act of 1984, were classified to the United States Code at "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s5601"},"text":"15 U.S.C. 5601","children":[],"tail":" et seq."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idec022eb0-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idec022eb1-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Communications Act of 1934, referred to in subsec. (b)(1), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1934-06-19/ch652"},"text":"act June 19, 1934, ch. 652","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/48/1064"},"text":"48 Stat. 1064","children":[],"tail":", which is classified principally to section 151 et seq. of Title 47, Telecommunications. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t47/s609"},"text":"section 609 of Title 47","children":[],"tail":" and Tables."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Foreign Trade Zones Act, referred to in subsec. (f), is ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1934-06-18/ch590"},"text":"act June 18, 1934, ch. 590","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/48/998"},"text":"48 Stat. 998","children":[],"tail":", which is classified generally to chapter 1A (§ 81a et seq.) of Title 19, Customs Duties. For complete classification of this Act to the Code, see Tables."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idec022eb2-3a70-11f1-9081-fe88c1712d53"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2015—Subsec. (g). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/114/90"},"text":"Pub. L. 114–90","children":[],"tail":" amended subsec. (g) generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “This chapter does not apply to—"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(1) a launch, reentry, operation of a launch vehicle or reentry vehicle, operation of a launch site or reentry site, or other space activity the Government carries out for the Government; or","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"“(2) planning or policies related to the launch, reentry, operation, or activity.”","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2010—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/314/s4/d/2"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–314, § 4(d)(2)","children":[],"tail":", (3)(S), successively renumbered "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t49/s70117"},"text":"section 70117 of title 49","children":[],"tail":" and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t51/s70117"},"text":"section 70117 of this title","children":[],"tail":" as this section."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (b)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/111/314/s4/d/5/T"},"text":"Pub. L. 111–314, § 4(d)(5)(T)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “chapter 601 of this title” for “the Land Remote Sensing Policy Act of 1992 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s5601"},"text":"15 U.S.C. 5601","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1998—Subsec. (a). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/303/s102/a/15/A"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–303, § 102(a)(15)(A)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or reentry site, or to reenter a reentry vehicle” after “operate a launch site”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/303/s102/a/15/B"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–303, § 102(a)(15)(B)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “or reentry” after “approval of a space launch”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/303/s102/a/15/C"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–303, § 102(a)(15)(C)","children":[],"tail":", amended heading and text of subsec. (f) generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “A launch vehicle or payload that is launched is not, because of the launch, an export for purposes of a law controlling exports.”"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (g)(1). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/303/s102/a/15/D/i"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–303, § 102(a)(15)(D)(i)","children":[],"tail":", substituted “reentry, operation of a launch vehicle or reentry vehicle, operation of a launch site or reentry site,” for “operation of a launch vehicle or launch site,”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (g)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/303/s102/a/15/D/ii"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–303, § 102(a)(15)(D)(ii)","children":[],"tail":", inserted “reentry,” after “launch,”."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"1996—Subsec. (b)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/287"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–287","children":[],"tail":" substituted “Land Remote Sensing Policy Act of 1992 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s5601"},"text":"15 U.S.C. 5601","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)” for “Land Remote-Sensing Commercialization Act of 1984 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t15/s4201"},"text":"15 U.S.C. 4201","children":[],"tail":" et seq.)”."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
